# Production Grade DevOps Platform

This project demonstrates a **production-grade DevOps platform** that includes infrastructure automation, container orchestration, CI/CD pipelines, security practices, monitoring, and centralized logging.

The goal is to simulate how real organizations design and operate cloud-native systems.

---

# Project Components

## Infrastructure

Infrastructure will be provisioned using Terraform.

Resources include:

- VPC
- subnets
- internet gateway
- NAT gateway
- EKS cluster
- container registry

---

## Application

A Python Flask application will provide basic functionality:

- user registration
- user login
- authentication using JWT
- persistent database storage

---

## Containerization

The application will be packaged into Docker containers.

---

## Kubernetes

The application will be deployed to Kubernetes using Helm charts.

---

## CI/CD

CI/CD pipelines will automate:

- build
- testing
- container image creation
- security scanning
- deployment

---

## Observability

The platform will implement observability using:

- Prometheus
- Grafana
- Loki
- Alertmanager

---

## Security

Security practices include:

- IAM access control
- container vulnerability scanning
- secrets management
- Kubernetes RBAC
- network policies

---

